At visit 2, the subjects had median daytime symptoms of 3 d/wk, nighttime symptoms 3 times a month, and required rescue albuterol for 1-day duration. Compared with baseline, a significant increase in log exhaled NO (+0.76), and decrease in lung function (FEV1 % predicted, −24; FEV1/FVC, −12%;, and FEF25-75 % predicted, −34), was noted at the time of exacerbation (all P values <.001) (Tables II
and III
).
